    "title": "\ud83d\ude80 Post 16: The Zero-Downtime Pipeline",
    "text": "\"I push code to production 5 times a day. If I break it, nobody notices.\"\nThere is nothing scarier than hitting \"deploy\" on a Friday afternoon. When I launched calculator-all.com, I knew I would be making constant adjustments to the 100+ formulas. \nI couldn't afford a single minute of downtime. So, I built an automated pipeline that catches my mistakes before they reach the main branch. \nRun calculations day or night with extreme uptime: https://calculator-all.com",
